453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.00d881eb-197b-40cb-8d6a-d2a7b6e0f0d6.prompt=User Identifier 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.13e847dc-2157-4440-ae23-095deed9d8c3.prompt=Artifact ID 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.1a04905f-d0d3-4427-b304-ed288b09eccd.prompt=User Identifier 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.1c634fcd-f8ab-4539-9f6e-6640bae4a1d9.description=This workflow adds/ updates the component properties to Instance using Artifact APIs.

onlyUpdate\: yes/no 
yes - To update values of existing properties 
no - To add and/or update properties

keyValuePairs\:
If you want to Add/update new properties\:
 <property>
 <name>property1</name>
 <scope>
 <name>PUBLIC</name>
 </scope>
 <valueType>
 <name>INTEGER</name>
 </valueType>
 <values>
 <value>5</value>
 </values>
 </property> 
 <property>
 <name>property2</name>
 <scope>
 <name>PUBLIC</name>
 </scope>
 <valueType>
 <name>STRING</name>
 </valueType>
 <values>
 <value>abc xyz</value>
 </values>
 </property>

If you want to only update the values of existing properties\:
 <property>
 <name>property1</name>
 <values>
 <value>5</value>
 </values>
 </property> 
 <property>
 <name>property2</name>
 <values>
 <value>abc xyz</value>
 </values>
 </property> 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.29ebc7a6-3de4-48f8-a8b8-550d099044eb.prompt=User Identifier 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.5b194e08-3190-44d4-bb72-2a2cb14504b8.description=Waits for the job to reach a specific state. If no state is specified, then this will wait for the job to reach an end state.

Inputs\:
coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core.
corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on.
coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS.
coreUsername - The username for host.
corePassword - The password for host.
coreVersion - The version of SAS to use.
jobID - The id of the job.
status - The status to wait for the job to reach. If none is specified this will wait until the job is no longer running.
timeout - The maximum number of milliseconds to wait for the job. If not specified, 1 hour is used.
frequency - The frequency, in milliseconds, with which the operation will check if the job has reached the specified state (or an end state). The default value is 5000 ms.

Responses\:
failure - Something went wrong.
success - The operation completed successfully. 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.6d0d52e5-8952-4d8b-8b27-6c0810b3fcbb.prompt=User Identifier 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.8d94e553-20ac-4908-80e1-8f81fbe2d0e0.description=This workflow updates the Process Instance State using PEM API.

Inputs\:
_PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id
_processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State)



Result\:
_processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State
 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.9b1e5398-618f-4d10-a125-4bccb59da526.prompt=Process Instance ID 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.a68a8210-6c23-4d40-8711-ab7d8ba04d5d.description=Reboot the given Server managed in SA. 

Inputs\:
coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core.
corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on.
coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS.
coreUsername - The username for host.
corePassword - The password for host.
coreVersion - The version of SAS to use.
agent - Name of the server to reboot now.
wait - An integer value specifying How many milliseconds should be waited for the job to finish. If not specified the job is started, but may not have finished.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
returnResult - The id of the job created. 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.a6f7429e-fc88-40bc-bc5d-0c85c953996d.prompt=Component ID 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.b0326e8a-7963-40d0-b465-ffb35d9a2c9f.prompt=Process Instance ID 453e93cf-16f8-4d1f-b46c-239c4bb59c3e.bdd9d49d-40da-42e8-84ec-169aeb236b7a.description=This workflow updates the Process Instance State using PEM API.

Inputs\:
_PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id
_processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State)



Result\:
_processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State
